        <mxCell id="Ax6jmUyKDm1l92f0dxil-56" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#232F3E;" value="Architecture Notes" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="160" x="410" y="630" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="Ax6jmUyKDm1l92f0dxil-57" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=10;fontColor=#232F3E;" value="Production Flow:&#xa;1. User loads React app from CloudFront/S3&#xa;2. User authenticates with Cognito User Pool (gets JWT)&#xa;3. Frontend exchanges JWT for AWS credentials via Identity Pool&#xa;4. Frontend generates SigV4 presigned WebSocket URL&#xa;5. Browser connects to AgentCore via wss:// with auth in URL&#xa;6. Bidirectional audio/text streaming with Nova Sonic model&#xa;&#xa;Local Development Flow:&#xa;• debug.html connects directly to local Python agent&#xa;• Uses ws://localhost:8080/ws (no authentication)&#xa;• For testing and debugging only&#xa;&#xa;Key Technologies:&#xa;• WebSocket for real-time bidirectional streaming&#xa;• SigV4 signing for AWS authentication&#xa;• Cognito for user management and AWS credential vending&#xa;• Nova Sonic for voice-to-voice AI interactions" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="190" width="440" x="410" y="660" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
